{
  "texts": [
    "This is necessary to express the fact that, in four spacetime dimensions, a quantum field theory treatment of hadron form factors introduces such scaling violations.",
    "Neglecting the extra suppression, the transforms yield spurious short-distance divergences -see, e.g., Ref.",
    "[94,Fig. 4].The required completions can be achieved by fitting the form factor results obtained using the algebraic Ansätze with the following function:F (y = Q 2 / 2 I)=F 0 1+b 1 y 1+b 2 y+b 3 y 2 1 + a 0 y 1 + a 0 y ln (1 + a 0 y).",
    "(27)where F 0:= F (y = 0).",
    "The coefficients are listed in Table 3.Charge and mass distribution Breit frame density profiles, calculated from F = F P, θ P 2, respectively, are fairly straightforward."
  ]
